<a name="10">[10]</a> <a href="#10" id=10>Many potential astronomy applications require access at the granularity of objects rather than entire files.</a>
<a name="11">[11]</a> <a href="#11" id=11>Nevertheless, there are clear grammatical rules for encapsulating complex information in a machine-readable form, and there are style sheets that render XML data to various easily understandable formats.</a>
